result.formatted_address: 26 Mong Kok Rd, Mong Kok, Hong Kong
result.name: Lucky Dessert

reviews.text:
Bad service..
Every person seated must order.
Dessert is lousy.
The signature items are mango theme

Honestly it was underwhelming. The waffles were dry as dust and the mango with rice balls didn’t help either. The rice balls were hard like eating marbles and the mango was too sour. If that were not enough, the price was exorbitant to say the least. I’d rather go to a stall than here. Looks great though, but as they say, looks can be deceiving. Sorry.

Dessert was extremely bad. We had mango pomelo and it tasted like water. They were able to price it at 52hkd for dessert that is obviously pre-made as they were not able to alter the taste for us. Not recommended at all. Don't waste your money
Deserts taste good. Excellent service, the owner has good manner and is very polite. This is not very common in Hong Kong unfortunately.

勁難食！個甜品好明顯係至少前晚已經整好。d西米浸左勁耐d口感好差。個waffle勁乾d味好怪 每食一口都乾到好難受。而且一黎既時候只係溫溫地， 可能都係一早已經整好。
又難食又貴。 送比我都唔食。 最後食左一半就走左。
Garbage! Desserts were extremely bad. They were obviously pre-made. Bad quality and expensive.

Bad service..

Dessert is lousy.
員工態度一般，經理冇禮貌，仲會突然大叫，嚇親咗唔少客...窩夫好硬，班戟見到佢哋廚房直接用手拎...有啲材料用大陆品牌(如牛奶蒙牛)，餐具唔乾淨，唔講衛生。
